                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d01">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r"/> (haräg);
                      <locus target="#85v #91v #107v #110r #121r #159v #178r"/> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#117v #118r #126v #127r #127v #132v #133v #135v #137v #148v #149r #150r #150v #151r"/>, etc. (connected full stops);
                      <locus target="#180r"/> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc type="GuestText">
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso)"/> is from rejected leaf from another book used as a protection sheet. It contains excerpts from the Night Hours of <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3575Mashaf"/>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#159v"/> Note of ownership: “This book belongs to Arǝk Sǝlus. Anyone who steals or erases it, may he be cursed by the authority of Saints Peter and Paul.
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#181r #181v #182r #182v"/> are from a rejected leaf of another book with text of an unidentifiable prayer
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 has the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters only for aleph
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#37r #57r #63r #64r"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #40v #50v #148r"/>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#131v"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#3v #5v #25r #90r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate
                      aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line
                      of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the
                      next line (e.g., <locus target="#61r #87r #90v"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
